<br>
If the Bible is full of rampant exaggerations, how could Christianity have risen in the areas where Jesus performed these exaggerated mircales?  I mean if you told me you could raise the dead and came to my house and we talked, and then suddenly 40 people said that you made a monkey fly out of your ass while I was there, I for sure would not believe in your status as a diety, in fact I'd say &quot;I was there, and that's not what happened.&quot;  But there are no recounts of the life of Christ written anywhere near the time of his existance.  But then again, lack of proof does not necessarily equate to lack of argument, so I'll give you that it is possible.<br>
